n, k = map(int, input().split())
    arr = list(map(int, input().split()))
    arr.sort()
    ans = 0
    for i in range(n):
        if arr[i] <= k:
            k -= arr[i]
            ans += 1
        else:
            break
    print(ans)

n, k = map(int, input().split())
    prices = list(map(int, input().split()))
    prices.sort()
    i = 0
    count = 0
    while k > 0 and i < n:
        if k - prices[i] >= 0:
            k -= prices[i]
            count += 1
        else:
            break
        i += 1
    print(count)
